{
  "page": "Chestnut",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For the type of tree, see <a href=\"/index.php/Chestnut_tree\" title=\"Chestnut tree\">Chestnut tree</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Arlan_of_Pennytree\" title=\"Arlan of Pennytree\"><img alt=\"Arlan of Pennytree.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d8/Arlan_of_Pennytree.svg/50px-Arlan_of_Pennytree.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d8/Arlan_of_Pennytree.svg/75px-Arlan_of_Pennytree.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d8/Arlan_of_Pennytree.svg/100px-Arlan_of_Pennytree.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Chestnut</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\"><img alt=\"Dunk.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/78/Dunk.svg/50px-Dunk.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/78/Dunk.svg/75px-Dunk.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/78/Dunk.svg/100px-Dunk.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Owners</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Arlan_of_Pennytree\" title=\"Arlan of Pennytree\">Arlan of Pennytree</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Species</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">Horse</a> <small>(stot)</small></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Gender</th><td>\nUncertain<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\nIn&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_210_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">210&#160;AC</a>,&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Hedge_Knight\" title=\"The Hedge Knight\">The Hedge Knight</a></i> (appears)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Sworn_Sword\" title=\"The Sworn Sword\">The Sworn Sword</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Chestnut</b> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horse</a>, a stot owned by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arlan_of_Pennytree\" title=\"Arlan of Pennytree\">Arlan of Pennytree</a>, and later Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chestnut&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Chestnut was old, and swaybacked.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The stot was too old to be worth much,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> but he was patient, and never bucked or bit.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The horse's gait was less easy than the palfrey <a href=\"/index.php/Sweetfoot\" title=\"Sweetfoot\">Sweetfoot</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chestnut&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Dunk\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dunk\">Dunk</a> became Ser Arlan's <a href=\"/index.php/Squire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Squire\">squire</a>, he would ride the <a href=\"/index.php/Hedge_knight\" title=\"Hedge knight\">hedge knight</a>'s stot Chestnut,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> while Arlan rode his palfrey Sweetfoot. (Arlan's destrier, <a href=\"/index.php/Thunder\" title=\"Thunder\">Thunder</a>, was not ridden except in <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney\" title=\"Tourney\">tourneys</a> and battle.) Arlan frequently told Dunk that a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> should never love a horse, since they might die under him, but he loved his horses anyway. Arlan often spent his last <a href=\"/index.php/Currency\" title=\"Currency\">copper</a> on an apple for Chestnut, or oats for Sweetfoot and Thunder.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/209_AC\" title=\"209 AC\">209&#160;AC</a>, the aged Arlan died from a chill on the way to <a href=\"/index.php/Ashford_Meadow\" title=\"Ashford Meadow\">Ashford Meadow</a>, and Dunk took ownership of Chestnut, along with Thunder and Sweetfoot. At first Dunk debated selling Thunder and Chestnut, and keeping Sweetfoot, but then he decided to attend the <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney_at_Ashford_Meadow\" title=\"Tourney at Ashford Meadow\">tourney at Ashford Meadow</a> as the knight Ser Duncan the Tall. To afford a suit of <a href=\"/index.php/Armor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Armor\">armor</a>, Dunk reluctantly decided to sell Sweetfoot, as Chestnut was not worth much, and Thunder would be needed for the <a href=\"/index.php/Joust\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Joust\">joust</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Dunk rode Sweetfoot to <a href=\"/index.php/Ashford\" title=\"Ashford\">Ashford</a>, finding her gait easier than Chestnut's, but still tiring. On the way, he stopped at an inn, where Dunk first met Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a>, disguised as \"Egg\", when he asked the (assumed) <a href=\"/index.php?title=Stableboy&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Stableboy (page does not exist)\">stableboy</a> to rub down Sweetfoot and feed his horses. On the tourney grounds, Dunk was arrested when he attacked Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aerion_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerion Targaryen\">Aerion Targaryen</a>, who was assaulting <a href=\"/index.php/Tanselle\" title=\"Tanselle\">a girl</a> that Dunk had met earlier. While Dunk was imprisoned, Egg and their friend <a href=\"/index.php/Raymun_Fossoway\" title=\"Raymun Fossoway\">Raymun Fossoway</a> took care of Chestnut and Thunder.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Maekar_Targaryen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maekar Targaryen\">Maekar Targaryen</a> allowed his son Aegon to officially become Dunk's <a href=\"/index.php/Squire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Squire\">squire</a>, Egg rode Chestnut when they traveled, while Duncan rode Thunder.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Chestnut died in <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>, during the desert crossing between the <a href=\"/index.php/Prince%27s_Pass\" title=\"Prince&#39;s Pass\">Prince's Pass</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Vaith\" title=\"Vaith\">Vaith</a>. Dunk wanted to bury his old friend,  but their Dornish companions would not wait, and so Chestnut's corpse was left to the <a href=\"/index.php/Dog\" title=\"Dog\">sand dogs</a>. Afterwards, Dunk and Egg rode double on Thunder, until Egg's brother gave them <a href=\"/index.php/Maester_(mule)\" title=\"Maester (mule)\">Maester</a> the <a href=\"/index.php/Mule\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mule\">mule</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Later, at <a href=\"/index.php/Standfast\" title=\"Standfast\">Standfast</a>, Dunk dreamed of burying Chestnut in the sands while crying, as the Dornish <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a> and others stood by and mocked him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chestnut&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Egg</b>: <a href=\"/index.php/Maekar_Targaryen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maekar Targaryen\">My lord father</a> says I am to serve you.<br />\n<b>Dunk</b>: Serve you, <i>ser</i>. You can start by saddling the horses. Chestnut is yours, treat her kindly. I don't want to find you on <a href=\"/index.php/Thunder\" title=\"Thunder\">Thunder</a> unless I put you there.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Chestnut, his name was Chestnut, and he bore me on his back for years, and never bucked or bit. The old <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">stot</a> had looked a sorry thing beside the sleek <a href=\"/index.php/Sand_steed\" title=\"Sand steed\">sand steeds</a> that the <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornishmen</a> were riding, with their elegant heads, long necks, and flowing manes, but he had given all he had to give.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;dreaming of <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Weeping for a swaybacked stot? Why, lad, you never wept for me, who put you on his back.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;\"<a href=\"/index.php/Arlan_of_Pennytree\" title=\"Arlan of Pennytree\">Arlan of Pennytree</a>\" in <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan</a>'s dream</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chestnut&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Chestnut's gender switches between <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Hedge_Knight\" title=\"The Hedge Knight\">The Hedge Knight</a></i> and <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Sworn_Sword\" title=\"The Sworn Sword\">The Sworn Sword</a></i>. In <i>The Hedge Knight</i>, <a href=\"/index.php/Dunk\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dunk\">Dunk</a> calls the horse \"her\", but in <i>The Sworn Sword</i>, Chestnut is called \"him\". In the television adaptation <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Knight_of_the_Seven_Kingdoms_(TV_series)\" title=\"A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms (TV series)\">A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms</a></i>, Chestnut is called \"her\", as in the first novella.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chestnut&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsect